content.description: Work around the giant flake below the start of the crack (either left or right, though left seems to put one in a harder position). Lay back or finger lock if you can get them in; rattly at places as well. Hold it together with some good footwork and you're free into the trees that gaze over the top of this wall. Exit to the right down a shallow gully.
content.protection: Couple pads and spotters with long arms. I don't recommend doing this one alone.
content.location: The right and thinner of the two parallel cracks one sees upon arriving at the base of the Alien Wall.

content.description: This is a lesson in thin techniqual climbing, which is much different then its neighbors. Stand start on crimps on the seam that moves up and to the right.  Move up and right to a horizontal seam.  Some techniqual foot work allows you to make a big move to another horizontal seam.  More good foot work allows you to go for a crimp out left, fall here and you'll land on the small tree.  Make one more big move up and right back into the seam to a decent hold and then top out the slab.
content.protection: one or two pads; 1-2 spotters is a must, if you come off up high you are going to tumble down the hill
content.location: Ten feet left of Flight of the Navigator

content.description: Start on the left side of the giant flake, move up through the little roof and out onto the bomber hands crack. Breathe it out to the top and you're good to go.
content.location: The left of the 2 center cracks on the Alien Wall.

content.description: Start at the giant flake and climb out the hands crack to the right and around the corner.
content.location: The right crack on the Alien Wall.

climbs.name: Close Encounters of the Trad Kind

content.description: Start with an impossibly small crimp and a dish for your thumb, with feet on the huge ledge. A couple desperate moves deposit one into the amazing hand crack that finishes Flight of the Navigator. Time for the crimping men and women to pull out some traditional skills and jam to the top! Fun through and through!
content.location: Face climb just to the left of the two parallel cracks upon arriving. There is a low mono pocket to the right of the start that could help this go as a very difficult sit start.

content.description: Sit start on the farthest right side of the alian wall.  Either matched or with left had out in side pull slot. then move out to horizontal crack on face, or stay on faint arete. go up to large crack using cool sloping holds.  you could continue on the arete line for a harder scarier top out. maybe contrived but fun
content.protection: 1 pad.  more if you go straight out on the arete line.
content.location: faint arete on furthest right side of alian wall.

content.description: This is the next section of rock one is rewarded with after the short hike along the flagged trail. There are two cracks that run parallel up this wall directly in front of where the trail meets this wall. The rock slowly becomes less climbable to the left, while gaining height and more features to the right. All in all, about 50 ft. long, and 20 ft at the highest. Perfect and flat landing all along the base.
